(Gulf Area Office) UNICEF in Qatar requests CoE support to strengthen and operationalize a national coordination mechanism for youth under MSY’s leadership. Assistance is required to:
• Provide technical inputs to the design of governance arrangements, ToRs, and secretariat functions;
• Support MSY and UNICEF in developing a multi-year, costed implementation plan for the National Youth Policy, aligned with NDS3 and the SDGs;
• Assist in developing a youth data and indicator framework, including links to international indices;
• Provide technical guidance to help Qatar establish a UN-wide youth coordination arrangement that aligns UN support behind MSY priorities.

As Kenya transitions into the new Gavi 6.0 strategic period, the Ministry of Health—together with UNICEF Kenya—sees an urgent need to undertake a comprehensive Vaccine Program Optimization and Prioritization exercise. This will help the country align its immunization investments, strengthen program efficiency, and ensure that the forthcoming Gavi support is strategically targeted to maximize impact.
In this regard, we kindly request technical assistance from the Centre of Excellence to support Kenya in:

Conducting a structured diagnostic of key program bottlenecks and optimization opportunities;
Facilitating stakeholder consultations to inform prioritization and investment decisions;
Developing a clear, evidence‑driven prioritization framework that aligns with Gavi 6.0 requirements and Kenya’s Immunization Agenda; and
Supporting the integration of findings into national planning and resource mobilization processes.

